<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">By Amber Hovious, VP Marketing and Partnerships at Teamwork Commerce</p>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">It's that time of year when sales take on new horizons, and retailers have the opportunity to capitalize on fresh consumer enthusiasm during the holiday season. The festive period is one of the most important stretches of the year for retailers — Statista estimates US consumers spent approximately $923 billion during the 2023 holiday season, with 2024 expected to reach around $960 billion, a 4% increase. While it's critical to drive sales in the moment, retailers need to think long term and deploy strategies that help them thrive well after the season ends.</p>

<h2>Personalization becoming a game-changer</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">Personalized discounts help customers feel valued and drive long-term loyalty — but personalization is more than messaging and emails. It starts with merchants genuinely understanding their customers: preferences, purchasing habits, and styles. Customer relationship management (CRM) software gives retailers visibility into each shopper's activity, arming in-store associates with actionable data on preferences, sizing, and purchase history so every interaction can be tailored. Paired with loyalty schemes and personalized promotions, that data helps retailers build the kind of long-term relationships that turn a holiday shopper into a repeat customer.</p>

<h2>Turbocharging transactions</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">Today's retail landscape is fast-paced, and so are consumers. Self-checkout technology enables faster purchases, increasing the number of transactions a retailer can complete in a day, and frees in-store associates from the register to focus on delivering better customer experiences. RFID-powered self-checkout, which scans all items automatically with 100 percent accuracy, cuts the time spent on each purchase and smooths out the final touchpoint of the retail journey. As foot traffic increases during the holidays, mobile POS solutions let associates check customers out from anywhere on the floor, reducing queuing and giving staff the chance to offer tailored recommendations before completing the sale on the spot.</p>

<h2>Driving customer retention</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">Retailers want to build a loyal customer base, and the holiday season is a strong moment to start. The technology retailers use plays a key role in supporting that goal, helping convert seasonal foot traffic into long-term revenue. But technology can't replace the human touch — the retailers who succeed will be the ones who strike the right balance, keeping the human element central while using tech to perfect the process around it.</p>

<h2>A festive feast</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">The festive season remains one of the most important periods of the year for retailers. The brands that succeed this winter will be the ones that deliver speed, convenience, and genuinely high-quality in-store experiences.</p>
